cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.SY 

This paper is about improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks through heterogeneous bitwidth binarization. The paper focuses on analyzing the impact of different bitwidths on the accuracy and efficiency of the network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential hardware implementations of the proposed method, which falls under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses training techniques to optimize the bitwidths, which is related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
